issue.title: OS X file normalization is causing files not to be found

repository.name: rclone
repository.description: "rsync for cloud storage" - Google Drive, S3, Dropbox, Backblaze B2, One Drive, Swift, Hubic, Wasabi, Google Cloud Storage, Azure Blob, Azure Files, Yandex Files

issue.body:
I have a particular file that rclone isn't able to upload. The file's name from ls is:

10 - Who You Are ≠ Where You Are.m4a

Environment info below.

rclone version: v1.32

OS: OS X 10.11.6 64bit

Cloud Storage: Google Drive

Command: rclone -q -c --exclude-from $HOME/.rclone-exclude.conf sync Archived\ Music/Into\ It.\ Over\ It_/Standards/ gdrive:Archived\ Music/Into\ It.\ Over\ It_/Standards/
